2011-15%20metres%20(about%2050%20feet)%20and%20it%20must%20have%20weighed%201%20tonne.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EIIT%20Roorkee's%20Prof.%20Sunil%20Bajpai%20%26amp%3B%20Debajit%20Datta%20discovered%20Vasuki%20Indicus%2C%20a%2047-million-year-old%20snake%20species%20in%20Kutch%2C%20Gujarat.%20Estimated%20at%2011-15%20meters%2C%20this%20extinct%20snake%20sheds%20light%20on%20India's%20prehistoric%20biodiversity.%20Published%20in%20Scientific%20Reports.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FSnakeDiscovery%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23SnakeDiscovery%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FruLsfgPQCc%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FruLsfgPQCc%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20IIT%20Roorkee%20(%40iitroorkee)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fiitroorkee%2Fstatus%2F1781027428997173545%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EApril%2018%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20was%20published%20in%20'Scientific%20Reports'%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41598-024-58377-0%5C%22%3E'Springer%20Nature'%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Thursday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsidering%20its%20large%20size%2C%20Vasuki%20was%20a%20slow-moving%20ambush%20predator%20that%20would%20subdue%20its%20prey%20through%20constriction%20like%20anacondas%20and%20pythons.%20This%20snake%20lived%20in%20a%20marshy%20swamp%20near%20the%20coast%20at%20a%20time%20when%20global%20temperatures%20were%20higher%20than%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Debajit%20Datta%2C%20a%20postdoctoral%20researcher%20in%20palaeontology%20at%20IIT-Roorkee%20and%20the%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2024%2Fapr%2F18%2Ffossils-largest-snake-found-western-india%5C%22%3Etold%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fossil%20has%20been%20named%20after%20Vasuki%2C%20the%20snake%20king%20associated%20with%20Lord%20Shiva.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20size%20rivals%20Titanoboa%2C%20which%20once%20lived%20in%20Colombia%20around%2060%20million%20years%20ago.%20It%20measured%20about%2043%20feet%20in%20length%20and%20weighed%20more%20than%20one%20tonne.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20estimated%20body%20length%20of%20Vasuki%20is%20comparable%20to%20that%20of%20Titanoboa%2C%20although%20the%20vertebrae%20of%20Titanoboa%20are%20slightly%20larger%20than%20those%20of%20Vasuki.%20However%2C%20at%20this%20point%2C%20we%20cannot%20say%20if%20Vasuki%20was%20more%20massive%20or%20slender%20compared%20to%20Titanoboa%2C%26quot%3B%20Sunil%20Bajpai%2C%20a%20palaeontologist%2C%20professor%20at%20Roorkee%20and%20the%20study's%20co-author%2C%20told%20the%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20largest%20living%20snake%20today%20is%20Asia's%20reticulated%20python%20at%2010%20metres%20(33%20feet).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20fossil%20was%20found%20in%20an%20area%20that%20is%20dry%20and%20dusty%20today%2C%20it%20was%20swampy%20when%20Vasuki%20roamed%20the%20Earth%2C%20said%20Mr%20Bajpai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20gives%20scientists%20not%20only%20a%20closer%20look%20into%20the%20evolution%20of%20snakes%20but%20also%20a%20deeper%20understanding%20of%20how%20continents%20physically%20shifted%20over%20time%20and%20species%20dispersed%20across%20the%20globe%2C%20a%20per%20Scientific%20American.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713504420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fg0cic2po_vasuki-indicus_625x300_19_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fmove-over-titanoboa-fossil-of-largest-snake-to-have-ever-existed-found-in-gujarat-5474872%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20fossil%20has%20been%20named%20after%20Vasuki%2C%20the%20snake%20king%20associated%20with%20Lord%20Shiva.%20The%20largest%20living%