acher%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20will%20kids%20learn%20what%20not%20to%20do%20if%20we%20don't%20teach%20them%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mother%20and%20son%20at%20listening%20party%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20Silent%20Green%2C%20a%20former%20crematorium%20in%20Berlin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661f91eb10c6b0cde5f0383d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20and%20her%20son%20spent%20time%20at%20Berlin's%20green%20spaces%2C%20including%20this%20listening%20party%20on%20the%20grounds%20of%20Silent%20Green%2C%20a%20former%20crematorium%20in%20Berlin.%3Cp%3EJF%20Grossen%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EBerlin%20was%20affordable%20for%20raising%20a%20family%20and%20had%20great%20childcare%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20moved%20to%20Europe%20from%20New%20York%20City%20for%20work.%20We%20started%20in%20Amsterdam%2C%20moved%20to%20London%20%E2%80%94%20where%20my%20son%20was%20born%20%E2%80%94%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F13-things-that-surprised-a-londoner-in-berlin-2017-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erelocated%20to%20Berlin%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20he%20was%20just%20over%20a%20year%20old.%20We%20didn't%20speak%20German%20and%20had%20never%20considered%20living%20in%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20from%20the%20get-go%2C%20we%20were%20amazed%20by%20how%20much%20farther%20our%20money%20went%20in%20Berlin.%20Though%20rental%20inventory%20was%20tough%20to%20come%20by%2C%20we%20paid%20%242%2C900%20a%20month%20for%20a%20three-bed%2C%20two-bath%20duplex%20with%20a%20private%20roof%20deck%20and%20elevator%20%E2%80%94%20a%20wonderful%20amount%20of%20space%20to%20raise%20a%20child.%20That's%20half%20the%20price%20we're%20now%20paying%20for%20our%20much%20smaller%20two-bedroom%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-rent-keeps-hitting-record-highs-despite-migration-from-city-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapartment%20in%20Manhattan%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20also%20impressed%20by%20the%20affordability%20of%20Berlin's%20childcare.%20Starting%20from%20the%20age%20of%20one%2C%20all%20kids%20are%20entitled%20to%20a%20free%20day%20care%2Fpreschool%20combo%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fplaces-with-free-pre-k-preschool-2019-8%23in-berlin-germany-early-childhood-education-is-free-but-families-pay-for-school-meals-and-activities-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20Kita%2C%20or%20kindergarten%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20for%20a%20minimum%20of%205%20to%207%20hours%20a%20day%3B%20working%20parents%2C%20those%20looking%20for%20work%20or%20studying%2C%20or%20single%20parents%20are%20eligible%20for%20even%20more%3A%207%20to%209%20hours%20of%20daily%20care.%20The%20care%20is%20available%20year-round.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20son%20was%20supervised%20by%20three%20teachers%20and%20with%20the%20same%2010%20kids%20every%20year%2C%20which%20allowed%20him%20to%20make%20close%20friends.%20His%20school%20was%20also%20bilingual%20German-English%2C%20so%20he%20became%20fluent%20in%20German%20within%20a%20few%20years%2C%20even%20though%20we%20didn't%20speak%20it%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20unlike%20in%20most%20of%20the%20US%2C%20in%20Germnay%2C%20school%20up%20until%20the%20equivalent%20of%20first%20grade%20is%20play-based%20and%20very%20child-driven%2C%20with%20lots%20of%20time%20spent%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20public%20school%20in%20New%20York%20has%20been%20a%20huge%20change%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20arrived%20back%20in%20New%20York%2C%20my%20son%20started%20first%20grade%20in%20public%20school.%20He%20was%20quickly%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20more%20anonymous%20classroom%20of%20around%2030%20students%20with%20one%20teacher.%20He%20also%20had%20difficulty%20adjusting%20to%20all%20of%20the%20structure%20around%20the%20school%20day.%20He%20was%20used%20to%20spending%20more%20time%20outdoors%20and%20wandering%20around%20the%20classroom%20as%20he%20pleased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fschool-start-times-in-conflict-dont-mesh-with-work-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshocked%20to%20learn%20that%20school%20ended%20at%202%3A35%20p.m.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Now%20in%20order%20to%20work%20a%20full%20day%2C%20we%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20afterschool%20classes%20and%20find%20options%20for%20summer%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20didn't%20worry%20much%20about%20safety%20in%20Berlin.%20For%20such%20a%20large%20city%2C%20Berlin%20is%20exceedingly%20safe.%20In%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalresidenceindex.com%2Fhnwi-index%2Fsafety-index%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20Safety%20Index%20by%20Global%20Residence%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Berlin%20ranked%2046%2C%20while%20New%20York%20City%20was%20107.%20Over%20there%2C%20it's%20not%20uncommon%20to%20see%20kids%20walking%20on%20their%20own%20to%20school%20starting%20in%20first%20or%20second%20grade.%20Back%20in%20the%20US%2C%20we%20would%20never%20even%20think%20about%20letting%20our%20son%20take%20the%20short%20walk%20to%20school%20without%20adult%20supervision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThere%20have%20been%20positives%20of%20being%20back%20in%20New%20York%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freverse-culture-shock-moving-back-to-america-asia-singapore-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereverse%20culture%20shock%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20real%2C%20we%20do%20still%20love%20being%20back%20in%20New%20York.%20We%20appreciate%20the%20diversity%20compared%20to%20Germany%2C%20both%20ethnic%20and%20socio-economic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20take%20advantage%20of%20the%20numerous%20cultural%20opportunities%20for%20both%20kids%20and%20adults%2C%20such%20as%20museums%20and%20theater.%20And%20even%20though%20there%20aren't%20quite%20as%20many%20playgrounds%20as%20in%20Berlin%2C%20we%20enjoy%20the%20welcoming%20vibe%2C%20where%20it's%20easy%20for%20kids%20to%20make%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20also%20noticed%20more%20parents%20taking%20ownership%20of%20unruly%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGot%20a%20personal%20essay%20about%20relocating%20a%20family%20that%20you%20want%20to%20share%3F%20Get%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20editor%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aakarplus%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eakarplus%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgerman-vs-american-parenting-differences-school-safety-culture-shock-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713485641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661f8fa010c6b0cde5f037c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgerman-vs-american-parenting-differences-school-safety-culture-shock-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20an%20American%20mom%20raising%20her%20son%20in%20Berlin%2C%20she%20rarely%20saw%20parents%20correcting%20bad%20behavior.%20Now%2C%20living%20in%20New%20York%2C%20she's%20surprised%20by%20how%20many%20rules%20are%20enforced.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(%20Liz%20Humphreys)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgerman-vs-american-parenting-differences-school-safety-culture-shock-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2220%20Syrian%20pro-government%20forces%20killed%20in%20IS%20attacks%3A%20Monitor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713485340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109416267%2Cimgsize-514233.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22htt