%20and%20Chinese%20troop%20carriers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20the%20Army%20put%20in%20a%20large%20order%20before%20ensuring%20the%20first%20turrets%20worked%20properly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFearing%20that%20its%20Stryker%20armored%20vehicles%20were%20outgunned%20by%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20designs%2C%20the%20US%20Army%20had%20an%20idea%20for%20a%20quick%20fix%3A%20Develop%20an%20unmanned%20Stryker%20turret%20with%20a%2030-mm%20autocannon.%20But%20cutting%20corners%20in%20the%20%241%20billion%20project%20has%20led%20to%20hardware%20and%20software%20issues%20that%20mean%20the%20more%20lethal%20Strykers%20won't%20be%20available%20until%20at%20least%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20a%20year%20later%20than%20scheduled.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIn%20prioritizing%20cost%20savings%20and%20rapid%20fielding%2C%20the%20Army%20assumed%20additional%20production%20risks%20because%20it%20did%20not%20follow%20sound%20acquisition%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-24-106590%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThough%20Army%20leaders%20said%20in%20December%202023%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbreakingdefense.com%2F2023%2F12%2Fupgunned-strykers-software-problems-resolved-says-army-two-star%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esoftware%20issues%20had%20been%20fixed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20war%20clouds%20in%20Europe%20and%20Asia%20raise%20the%20prospect%20that%20Stryker%20units%20might%20go%20into%20battle%20against%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20armored%20vehicles%20that%20are%20more%20heavily%20armed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECompared%20to%20ultra-complex%20projects%20such%20as%20the%20F-35%20stealth%20fighter%2C%20developing%20a%20small%20remote-controlled%20turret%20for%20an%20armored%20vehicle%20should%20have%20been%20easy.%20The%20project%20began%20in%202015.%20Worried%20by%20growing%20tensions%20in%20Europe%20and%20more%20lethal%20Russian%20hardware%2C%20the%20Army's%202nd%20Cavalry%20Regiment%20%E2%80%94%20based%20in%20Germany%20%E2%80%94%20urgently%20requested%20heavier%20armament%20for%20the%20Stryker%2C%20a%20family%20of%20eight-wheel%20armored%20vehicles%20manufactured%20by%20General%20Dynamics%20Land%20Systems.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%20of%20the%20Stryker's%20normal%20armament%20of%20a%20.50-caliber%20or%207.62-mm%20machine%20gun%2C%20or%20a%2040-mm%20grenade%20launcher%2C%20troops%20wanted%20a%20cannon%20that%20can%20punch%20through%20enemy%20armor%20and%20hardened%20positions.%20Russia%20arms%20its%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farmyrecognition.com%2Frussia_russian_army_light_armoured_vehicle_uk%2Fbmp-3_ifv_armored_infantry_fighting_vehicle_technical_data.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBMP%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20series%20of%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicles%20with%2030-mm%2C%2073-mm%20or%20100-mm%20guns%2C%20while%20China's%20new%20heavy%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farmyrecognition.com%2Fweapons_defence_industry_military_technology_uk%2Fchina_launches_its_vn20_most_protected_and_armed_tracked_armored_ifv_in_its_category.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EVN-20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20troop%20carrier%20comes%20with%2030-mm%20or%20100-mm%20cannon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Army%20obliged%20in%202018%20with%20the%20Infantry%20Carrier%20Vehicle-Dragoon%2C%20which%20added%20a%20remote-controlled%2030-mm%20gun%20turret%20%E2%80%94%20manufactured%20by%20Norwegian%20firm%20Kongsberg%20%E2%80%94%20to%2091%20flat-bottom-hull%20versions%20of%20the%20Strykers.%20General%20Dynamics%20did%20the%20modifications%20under%20an%20existing%20contract%2C%20which%20allowed%20the%20Army%20to%20develop%20and%20field%20the%20upgrade%20in%20a%20relatively%20quick%20two%20years.%20The%20Army%20decided%20the%20next%20year%20to%20buy%20269%20unmanned%2030-mm%20turrets%2C%20under%20the%20Medium%20Caliber%20Weapons%20Systems%20(MCWS)%20program%2C%20at%20an%20estimated%20cost%20of%20%241.1%20billion.%20This%20would%20be%20enough%20to%20upgrade%20Strykers%20in%20three%20brigades%20of%2083%20vehicles%20each%2C%20plus%20an%20additional%2020%20for%20testing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20instead%20of%20simply%20fielding%20more%20Dragoons%2C%20the%20Army%20decided%20to%20make%20some%20changes.%20Instead%20of%20flat-bottomed%20Strykers%2C%20the%20turrets%20would%20be%20mounted%20on%20the%20double%20hull%20A1%20version%20that%20is%20more%20blast-resistant%20and%20could%20better%20bear%20the%20weight%20and%20power%20requirements%20of%20a%20gun%20turret.%20Instead%20of%20a%20Kongsberg%20MCT-30%20turret%2C%20the%20vehicles%20would%20receive%20a%20Samson%20turret%20made%20by%20Israeli%20firm%20Rafael.%20And%20instead%20of%20General%20Dynamics%2C%20the%20prime%20contractor%20would%20be%20Oshkosh%20Systems%2C%20whose%20bid%20was%20one-third%20or%20more%20lower%20than%20other%20contenders.%20However%2C%20the%20cannon%20would%20continue%20to%20be%20Northrop%20Grumman's%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DCO1EaIbXxzE%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EXM813%20chain%20gun%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20used%20on%20the%20Dragoon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Army%20also%20fast-tracked%20the%20project%2C%20which%20shouldn't%20have%20been%20an%20issue.%20%26quot%3BArmy%20officials%20stated%20that%20they%20chose%20to%20accelerate%20production%20of%20the%20Stryker%20MCWS%2C%20rather%20than%20begin%20system%20development%2C%20because%20the%20effort%20integrated%20mature%2C%20proven%20technologies%E2%80%94the%20Stryker%20Double-V%20Hull%20A1%20and%20the%2030-millimeter%20cannon%2C%26quot%3B%20GAO%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20problem%20was%20that%20the%20Army%20was%20in%20such%20a%20hurry%20that%20it%20neglected%20some%20basic%20precautions.%20For%20example%2C%20Oshkosh's%20turret%20%26quot%3Bwas%20not%20tested%20by%20soldiers%20in%20their%20intended%20environment%20during%20the%20evaluation%20of%20the%20samples%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20the%20vendors%20acted%20as%20the%20commanders%20and%20gunners%20during%20testing%20on%20a%20range.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20soldiers%20fire%20the%20Dragoon's%2030mm%20autocannon%20during%20a%202022%20exercise.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66218b4e20b15f0ff4295ee5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20fire%20the%20Dragoon's%2030mm%20autocannon%20during%20a%202022%20exercise.%3Cp%3EKevin%20Payne%2FUS%20Army%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENor%20was%20Oshkosh's%20demonstration%20turret%20built%20on%20the%20actual%20manufacturing%20line%20that%20would%20be%20used%20for%20full%20production.%20A%20big%20red%20flag%20should%20have%20been%20the%20glitches%20in%20the%20turret%20software%20that%20degraded%20the%2030-mm%20cannon's%20accuracy.%20Because%20the%20gunner%20operates%20the%20cannon%20remotely%20from%20inside%20the%20vehicle%2C%20using%20a%20video%20feed%20rather%20than%20the%20naked%20eye%2C%20accurate%20targeting%20software%20is%20important.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Army%20stated%20these%20risks%20were%20moderate%20because%20of%20Oshkosh%20Defense's%20assurance%20of%20a%20future%20software%20fix%2C%26quot%3B%20GAO%20said.%20%26quot%3BArmy%20officials%20acknowledged%20that%20they%20would%20not%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20evaluate%20the%20success%20of%20the%20software%20fix%20prior%20to%20awarding%20the%20production%20contract.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20perceived%20need%20to%20get%20improved%20vehicles%20to%20troops%20in%20the%20field%20is%20understandable.%20But%20what%20was%20unusual%20was%20that%20the%20Army%20%26quot%3Bput%20in%20delivery%20orders%20for%20all%20269%20vehicles%20before%20ensuring%20that%20production%20line%20issues%20were%20addressed%2C%26quot%3B%20Mona%20Sehgal%2C%20acting%20director%20of%20GAO's%20contracting%20and%20national%20security%20acquisitions%20team%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Army%20awarded%20Oshkosh%20the%20first%20order%20in%20June%202021%20for%2091%20MCWS%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20second%20order%20for%2083%20in%20July%202021%20and%20finally%2095%20in%20June%202022%2C%20according%20to%20GAO.%20The%20first%20turrets%20weren't%20actually%20delivered%20until%20July%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENormal%20practice%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20or%20the%20business%20world%20%E2%80%94%20would%20be%20to%20place%20an%20initial%20order%20to%20judge%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20product%2C%20before%20placing%20further%20orders.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Army%20had%20structured%20the%20agreement%20to%20allow%20that%20but%20chose%20not%20to%20execute%20it%20that%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Sehgal%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EMichael%20Peck%20is%20a%20defense%20writer%20whose%20work%20has%20appeared%20in%20Forbes%2C%20Defense%20News%2C%20Foreign%20Policy%20magazine%2C%20and%20other%20publications.%20He%20holds%20an%20MA%20in%20political%20science%20from%20Rutgers%20Univ.%20Follow%20him%20on%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.twitter.com%2F%40mipeck1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ETwitter%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fmipeck%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%