to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Dominique%20Raroha%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20working%20in%20insurance%20in%20Sicklerville%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20which%20is%20about%2023%20miles%20outside%20Philadelphia%2C%20who%20bought%20a%20duplex%20as%20her%20first%20home%20purchase.%20The%20conversation%20was%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20regret%20my%20decision%20to%20buy%20a%20duplex.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHonestly%2C%20it%20felt%20right.%20I%20always%20believe%20in%20going%20with%20a%20good%20gut%20feeling%2C%20and%20from%20start%20to%20finish%20throughout%20this%20whole%20process%20of%20buying%20it%2C%20I%20just%20had%20a%20good%20feeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomeownership%20was%20a%20huge%20goal%20of%20mine.%20I'm%20the%20type%20of%20person%20who%20likes%20to%20take%20on%20a%20lot%20more%20responsibility%2C%20so%20I%20was%20excited%20and%20ready%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20great-grandfather%20bought%20up%20a%20big%20piece%20of%20real%20estate%20in%20Voorhees%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20that%20piece%20of%20real%20estate%20gained%20value%20so%20much%20over%20time.%20Over%20the%20years%20stuff%20was%20sold%20off%2C%20we%20built%20houses%2C%20and%20we%20were%20able%20to%20subdivide%20that%20piece%20of%20property.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20total%2C%20I%20think%20that%20amount%20of%20real%20estate%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20once%20a%20dirt%20road%20and%20is%20now%20a%20major%20highway%20in%20South%20Jersey%20%E2%80%94%20had%20to%20be%20valued%20at%20a%20couple%20of%20million%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221153%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20professional%20headshot%20of%20a%20woman.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6620424c20b15f0ff428f8dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22865%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERaroha%20bought%20a%20duplex%20as%20her%20first%20home.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Dominique%20Raroha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20States%20is%20a%20capitalist%20society%2C%20and%20real%20estate%20goes%20up%20over%20time.%20It's%20how%20you%20build%20your%20retirement.%20It's%20how%20you%20build%20generational%20wealth.%20It%20gives%20you%20something%20to%20pass%20down%20to%20the%20next%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20buying%20my%20first%20property%2C%20I'm%20already%20talking%20to%20my%20lender%20about%20buying%20another.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20financial%20freedom%20of%20owning%20a%20duplex%2C%20buying%20another%20makes%20so%20much%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20tenant's%20%242%2C000-a-month%20rent%20pays%20most%20of%20my%20mortgage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20looked%20at%20single-family%20homes%2C%20condos%20%E2%80%94%20I%20was%20looking%20at%20all%20my%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20I%20view%20money%20and%20my%20personal%20finances%20comes%20down%20to%20what%20I%20can%20afford%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis.%20Is%20this%20purchase%20in%20my%20best%20interest%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20just%20wanted%20to%20maximize%20my%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20single-family%20home%20I%20put%20an%20offer%20on%20was%20a%20really%20good-sized%20home.%20It%20was%20very%20well-priced%2C%20so%20that's%20why%20it%20made%20sense%20to%20put%20that%20offer%20in.%20For%20the%20condo%20I%20put%20an%20offer%20on%2C%20I%20would've%20been%20paying%20under%20%241%2C000%20a%20month.%20But%20somebody%20else%20already%20made%20a%20higher%20offer%20and%20the%20same%20with%20the%20other%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20put%20other%20offers%20in.%20Many%20of%20them%20were%20not%20accepted%20because%20you're%20dealing%20with%20a%20multiple-offer%20situation.%20But%20the%20more%20offers%20I%20didn't%20get%20accepted%2C%20the%20better%20prepared%20I%20was%20for%20the%20next%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20this%20home%20came%20on%20the%20market%2C%20I%20didn't%20see%20it%20%E2%80%94%20I%20bought%20it%20sight%20unseen.%20That%20was%20why%20working%20with%20the%20real-estate%20agent%20I%20did%20made%20such%20a%20difference%20because%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20this%20house%2C%20are%20you%20sure%3F%26quot%3B%20She's%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%2015%20other%20offers.%20You%20need%20to%20do%20the%20math.%20I%20don't%20see%20you%20losing%20in%20this%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20lender%20and%20I%20talked%20about%20it%20and%20we%20came%20up%20with%20our%20offer%20number%20based%20on%20what%20I%20could%20afford%20on%20a%20monthly%20basis%20with%20rental%20income.%20And%20to%20be%20honest%2C%20we%20could%20have%20gone%20higher%20and%20still%20made%20a%20decent%20investment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20square%20footage%20is%20about%202%2C400.%20My%20unit%20has%20two%20bedrooms%20and%20one%20bath%20%E2%80%94%20and%20I%20also%20have%20a%20private%20garage.%20The%20upstairs%20unit%20has%20three%20bedrooms%20and%20two%20baths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20garage%20under%20renovation%20with%20a%20bar%20and%20arcade%20games.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F662041eb49058e6693571ea5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERaroha's%20garage%20which%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20being%20turned%20into%20a%20%26quot%3Bbarcade.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Dominique%20Raroha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20put%20in%20an%20offer%20for%20%24335%2C000%2C%20and%20it%20appraised%20for%20%24320%2C000%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20fill%20an%20appraisal%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20interest%20rate%20is%206.6%25.%20I%20did%20get%20it%20lowered%20because%20I%20had%20almost%20an%20800%20credit%20score%20at%20the%20time%20of%20closing.%20If%20it%20was%20a%20point%20more%2C%20which%20was%20the%20average%20going%20rate%2C%20the%20cost%20would've%20been%20that%20much%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mortgage%20itself%20is%20about%20%242%2C900%20a%20month%E2%80%94%20more%20on%20the%20%243%2C000%20side.%20My%20upstairs%20tenant%20pays%20me%20%242%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20boyfriend%20lives%20with%20me%2C%20and%20he%20helps%20contribute.%20I'm%20not%20%3Cem%3Emaking%3C%2Fem%3E%20him%20pay%20half%20my%20mortgage%2C%20but%20he%20does.%20So%20we%20split%20half%20of%20the%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOwning%20a%20duplex%20gives%20me%20a%20lot%20of%20options%20for%20my%20next%20move%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20buying%20the%20duplex%2C%20I%20was%20living%20with%20my%20best%20friend%2C%20who%20had%20purchased%20a%20home%2C%20and%20she%20rented%20out%20a%20room%20to%20me%20to%20help%20pay%20for%20her%20mortgage.%20I%20was%20paying%20around%20%24700%20to%20her.%20It%20was%20a%20really%20good%20living%20situation%20because%20she%20knew%20the%20whole%20time%20I%20was%20looking%20for%20houses.%20So%20I%20wasn't%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%20my%20God%2C%20am%20I%20going%20to%20break%20a%20lease%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20be%20proactive.%20You%20have%20to%20be%20in%20this%20market%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20if%20you're%20a%20younger%20buyer.%20Even%20if%20you%20don't%20feel%20like%20you're%20fit%20today%2C%20at%20least%20talking%20to%20a%20lender%20ahead%20of%20time%20will%20help%20tell%20you%20where%20you%20need%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20talking%20to%20my%20lender%20in%20June%20of%202022.%20We%20would%20discuss%20different%20houses%20on%20the%20market%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20it%20would%20make%20sense%2C%20or%20whether%20it%20would%20be%20a%20good%20investment.%20Then%20this%20house%20came%20up%2C%20and%20it%20was%20very%2C%20very%20quick.%20But%20because%20I%20was%20working%20with%20him%2C%20he%20already%20had%20all%20my%20financials%20on%20file.%20He%20already%20had%20everything%20ready%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20were%20to%20rent%20out%20my%20unit%20today%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20there's%20a%20similar%20unit%20down%20the%20street%20from%20mine%20with%20the%20same%20layout%20that%20rented%20for%20%241%2C900%20%E2%80%94%20then%20I%20would%20be%20making%20a%20pro