as%20mine.%20I%20used%20to%20tell%20him%20how%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%20for%20society.%20He%20secured%20a%20job%20as%20an%20errand%20boy%20for%20me%20in%20the%20college%20itself%20which%20helped%20me%20pay%20the%20fees%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20his%20vision%20that%20helped%20me%20connect%20with%20Baba%20Amte%2C%20the%20legendary%20social%20worker%20and%20activist%20who%20worked%20with%20people%20suffering%20from%20leprosy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20principal%20sent%20me%20to%20him%2C%20seeking%20help%20for%20my%20vision.%20I%20used%20to%20go%20to%20his%20addresses%20and%20lectures%20to%20understand%20how%20one%20can%20help%20other%20people%20on%20a%20macro%20level.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Was%20called%20a%20fool%20behind%20my%20back%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20his%20graduation%2C%20he%20moved%20back%20to%20his%20village%20in%20Latur%20district%20to%20help%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F64071%2Fvellore-underprivileged-orphans-hope-house-college-education%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderprivileged%20people%20gain%20employment.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20getting%20my%20hands%20dirty%20on%20the%20field%20but%20no%20one%20could%20understand%20what%20I%20was%20doing.%20I%20was%20the%20first%20one%20to%20graduate%2C%20they%20expected%20me%20to%20do%20some%20job.%20They%20could%20not%20understand%20why%20I%20would%20come%20back%20to%20the%20village.%20They%20considered%20me%20a%20failure%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDemotivated%20by%20all%20the%20comments%2C%20he%20moved%20to%20Pune.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20disheartened%20and%20lacked%20direction%20in%20my%20work.%20I%20moved%20to%20Pune%20seeking%20help%20from%20other%20social%20workers%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaba%20Amte%20then%20suggested%20that%20he%20should%20first%20become%20financially%20independent%20and%20become%20a%20teacher.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20a%20school%20for%20the%20blind%20in%20front%20of%20my%20college%2C%20and%20once%20I%20completed%20my%20degree%2C%20I%20started%20to%20teach%20the%20kids%20there.%20It%20was%20there%20that%20I%20learnt%20that%20the%20kids%20get%20moved%20from%20one%20organisation%20to%20another%20constantly%2C%20either%20due%20to%20financial%20difficulties%20or%20lack%20of%20infrastructure.%20This%20hampered%20their%20growth%20and%20gave%20me%20the%20idea%20to%20do%20something%20to%20help%20people%20with%20visual%20impairments%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20this%20idea%20in%20mind%20of%20creating%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ESwadhar%20Kendra%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20in%20rural%20areas%20and%20villages%2C%20he%20left%20the%20city%20again.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20idea%20was%20that%20I%20wanted%20these%20children%20to%20get%20training%20and%20give%20them%20work%20opportunities%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20decided%20to%20leave%20the%20school%20and%20move%20back%20to%20the%20village%2C%20a%20student%20of%20his%20who%20also%20worked%20for%20him%2C%20decided%20to%20move%20too.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20could%20sing%20and%20dance%20well%2C%20and%20I%20used%20his%20art%20to%20grab%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20villagers.%20The%20%3Cem%3Esarpanch%20%3C%2Fem%3Etook%20us%20to%20the%20governor%20to%20get%20us%20a%20piece%20of%20land%20to%20stay%20and%20work%20on%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20foundation%20stone%20of%20what%20later%20became%20Grameen%20Shramik%20Pratishthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20got%20a%2040%C3%9740%20sq%20ft%20piece%20of%20land%20and%20we%20built%20a%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98jhopadi%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3E(hut).%20We%20would%20make%20bedsheets%20and%20blankets%20in%20the%20hut%20and%20then%20sell%20them.%20People%20were%20intrigued%20as%20to%20how%20a%20partially-impaired%20or%20blind%20person%20could%20do%20such%20a%20thing%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWord%20started%20spreading.%20Soon%2C%20more%20and%20more%20visually%20impaired%20people%20started%20to%20get%20in%20touch%20with%20him.%20%E2%80%9CI%20could%20finally%20see%20my%20dream%20shaping%20up.%20Soon%2C%20we%20were%20living%20with%20many%20more%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F99690%2Fgurugram-student-innovation-visually-impaired-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20visually%20impaired%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fleather-13-1712585674.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20NGO%20helps%20people%20with%20disability%20find%20jobs.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fleather-13-1712585674.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fleather-13-1712585674-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fleather-13-1712585674-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fleather-13-1712585674-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F04%2Fleather-13-1712585674-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-346857%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20NGO%20helps%20people%20with%20disability%20find%20jobs.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20the%20activities%20came%20to%20a%20halt%20when%20the%20area%20was%20hit%20by%20heavy%20rains%20and%20a%20massive%20flood%3B%20everything%20was%20washed%20away.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20too%20many%20people%20staying%