s%3A%20Anand%20Mishra.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713166036000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D347227%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Observing%20the%20year-round%20demand%20for%20lemons%2C%20Anand%20Mishra%20switched%20from%20growing%20traditional%20crops%20like%20wheat%2C%20paddy%2C%20and%20peas%20to%20cultivating%20lemons%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20With%20his%20two-acre%20farm%20now%20yielding%20Rs%207%20lakh%20in%20profits%2C%20he%20explains%20the%20reasoning%20behind%20this%20'unconventional'%20change.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F347227%2Ffarmer-lemon-man-of-raebareli-uttar-pradesh-anand-mishra-earning-five-times-more-in-lakhs%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20to%20Grow%20Pepper%2C%20Clove%2C%20Turmeric%20%26amp%3B%2015%20Types%20of%20Indian%20Spices%20At%20Home%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ELocated%20close%20to%20the%20foothills%20of%20the%20Himalayas%2C%20Roorkee-based%20Dr%20Anshu%20Rathi%E2%80%99s%20kitchen%20smells%20heavenly.%20From%20cumin%E2%80%99s%20earthy%20aroma%20to%20refreshing%20fennel%20and%20pungent%20fenugreek%20seeds%20%E2%80%93%20her%20kitchen%20evokes%20the%20rustic%20charm%20of%20Indian%20spices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20I%20crush%20%3Cem%3Ekasuri%20methi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(dried%20fenugreek%20leaves)%20on%20my%20palms%2C%20it%20leaves%20a%20very%20strong%20and%20tantalising%20smell.%20My%20husband%20is%20in%20awe%20of%20the%20fennel%20tea%20that%20I%20make.%20It%20feels%20so%20refreshing%20and%20tasty%20as%20it%20does%20not%20have%20any%20preservatives%20and%20colours%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dr%20Anshu%20(36)%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20doctor%20by%20profession%2C%20she%20has%20established%20a%20lavish%20garden%20of%20up%20to%20400%20plants%20of%20fruits%2C%20vegetabl